# CI validation gates

After **implementing code changes** (files edited this session), run the
**minimal** `make` targets for touched paths. Do not run blind `make check`
unless full CI parity is required.

**Do not run validation** during Plan mode, Ask mode, research-only turns, or
when no files were edited this session. See
[agent-workflow.mdc](agent-workflow.mdc).

| If you changed | Run after implementation |
|----------------|------------------------|
| `**/*.rs` | `make fmt-check clippy` then `make cargo-test` (or scoped `cargo test -p <crate> --features vlz/testing`) |
| `scripts/**/*.py`, `tests/scripts/**` | `make lint-python test-scripts` |
| `scripts/**/*.sh` | `make lint-shell` |
| `architecture/**/*.mmd` | `make check-doc-diagrams` |
| config keys, `verilyze.conf.example` | `make check-config-docs` |
| `man/**`, CLI help strings | `make check-manpages` |
| `packaging/**` | `make check-packaging` |
| `Cargo.toml`, `Cargo.lock`, `deny.toml` | `make cargo-check-locked`, `make deny-check`, `make check-third-party-licenses`, `make check-sbom` |
| `pyproject.toml` | `make check-sbom` |
| New source files | `make check-headers` |
| Production behavior change | `make unit-tests`; before PR also `make check-pr` |
| Non-behavior change before PR | `make check-fast` (~2-4 min; includes `check-super-linter-native`) |
| Super-linter paths (below) | `make super-linter` (Docker, ~3-10 min; must exit 0 when touched) |
| **Full CI parity** | `make -j check` |

Super-linter paths: `.github/**`, `*.{yml,yaml}`, `biome.json`, `renovate.json`,
`.gitleaks.toml`, `.commitlintrc.json`, `scripts/super-linter.sh`,
`packaging/**/*.env`, `packaging/**/Dockerfile`.

Incremental: `make super-linter`. Full tree (nightly): `make super-linter-full`.

## Clippy (Rust only)

- Single crate: `cargo clippy -p <crate> --all-targets -- -D warnings`
- Cross-crate or workspace `Cargo.toml`: `make clippy`
- Before PR (production behavior): `make check-pr` (sequential check-fast +
  coverage-quick)
- Before PR (non-behavior): `make check-fast` (includes clippy)

Do **not** run clippy or super-linter inside Cursor hooks. Run them via shell
when paths require it. Launch a **shell** subagent for long checks only when
checks failed or the user asked; do not spawn one after read-only turns.

## Do not skip

- SPDX headers; trailing blank line after header block
- Signed commits + DCO before push (`make check-dco`, `make check-signatures`)
- Conventional commit subject ~50 chars (CONTRIBUTING)

## Subagents

- `explore`: broad codebase questions (readonly)
- `shell`: long checks when validation is required (`check-pr`, `check-fast`,
  clippy fix-and-retry, super-linter in background)
- `ci-investigator`: one failed GitHub Actions job on a PR

Hooks opt-out: `VLZ_CURSOR_HOOKS_DISABLE=1`.

## Releases (explicit human request only)

Do **not** bump versions, create release tags, or push `v*` tags unless the
user explicitly asked for a release in the current conversation. Follow
[`.cursor/skills/release-prepare/SKILL.md`](.cursor/skills/release-prepare/SKILL.md).
Confirm target version and publish intent before tagging/pushing.
